features.name: PNP_UDP_1 Catalyzes the irreversible cleavage of the glycosidic bond in both 5'-methylthioadenosine (MTA) and S- adenosylhomocysteine (SAH AdoHcy) to adenine and the corresponding thioribose, 5'-methylthioribose and S-ribosylhomocysteine, respectively
- Forms oxaloacetate, a four-carbon dicarboxylic acid source for the tricarboxylic acid cycle
- Cleaves both 3' and 5' ssDNA extremities of branched DNA structures
